news.title: New York Life Insurance to invest Rs 196 crore in a commercial project of Max Estates in Noida
news.para: The land spread across 4 acre in Sector 129, Noida was acquired by Max Estates, the real estate arm of Max group, from Axis Bank for Rs 220 crore in August.

news.title: Bombay HC appoints court receiver for OJAS Tradelease's Ahmedabad mall
news.para: The court has also restrained the Future Group company OJAS Tradelease and Mall Management from creating any third-party rights or lien on the property until the final ruling.

news.title: Delhi HC quashes ED's ECIR against Indiabulls Housing and its employees
news.para: ​The high court, in an order passed on Monday, also set aside the Look Out Circulars (LOC) issued against those employees and said there shall be no search, seizure or summons arising out of the Enforcement Case Information Report (ECIR).

news.title: Birla Corporation commits $1 billion to ramp capacity to 30 MT in eight years
news.para: ​The plan entails the installation of a four-million tonne per annum each capacity in a greenfield project and brownfield expansion. While a two million tonne output increase will come from the de-bottlenecking of existing facilities.

news.title: SBI moves NCLT to initiate insolvency against Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Jaiprakash Associates' lease for some of the land under the jurisdiction of Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority has also been cancelled as the company failed to pay the dues.

news.title: Germany's Vonovia maintains right to evict tenants even as energy bills explode
news.para: In a step-by-step model, the company would reach out individually to the tenant to look for a solution for late payment, including informing them about how to obtain state aid, with an eviction notice seen as a last resort.

news.title: Government-owned firm steps in to complete four China Evergrande projects
news.para: Evergrande has introduced Shenzhen Longgang Ancheng Investment Operation Co Ltd into four developments situated in the Longgang district.

news.title: Amrapali homebuyers asked to form association to take over maintenance of the project
news.para: The court receiver has asked the apartment owners to come forward to take over the project’s maintenance as neither NBCC nor the contractor will manage it.

news.title: Delhi: Panel finds violations during construction of shopping complex
news.para: The report was submitted following National Green Tribunal’s (NGT) order in July after residents of Ashok Niketan, a residential area near Anand Vihar, filed a petition pointing out health impacts due to the construction.

news.title: Blackstone sells 7.7 crore shares of Embassy REIT for $325 million
news.para: Abu Dhabi Investment Authority (ADIA) and Kotak have bought shares in the block deal. ICICI Prudential, HDFC Life and Kotak Mutual Fund are among other buyers.

news.title: Registration of residential sales in Kolkata dips 15% year-on-year in August 2022
news.para: In all, 6,238 residential properties were registered in Kolkata Metropolitan Area in August 2022, down from 6,709 in July 2022. In August 2021 that had witnessed record registrations, the figure was 7,316.

news.title: TCP act amendments scrapped along with clearances under section 16B: Goa minister
news.para: State Town and Country Planning Minister Vishwajit Rane said the amendments were being scrapped as even keeping them in abeyance would have caused more doubts among people on the intention of the government.

news.title: Orient Bell rises 6% as firm completes expansion at Hoskote plant
news.para: With this, the total capacity of the company has increased from 32 MSM per annum to 33.8 MSM per annum including 10 MSM per annum of the associated entities.

news.title: Houses in Raipur to have digital door numbers, unique IDs
news.para: With the installation of digital door numbers on all 3.15 lakh houses in the city, the landlord will get 26 types of essential and emergency services, including payment of various taxes, door-to-door garbage collection and tap connection, conveniently sitting at home.

news.title: HCC jumps 10% after completion of debt resolution plan
news.para: HCC has completed its debt resolution plan, duly supported by 23 banks, the company said in a regulatory filing. "The resolution plan has carved out a significant portion of its debt along with commensurate assets from its balance sheet."
